value.value: A root differentiation zone that is part of a primary root.
A root differentiation zone that is part of a lateral root.
A root cap that is part of a primary root tip.
A root cap that is part of a lateral root tip.

label.value: central root cap of lateral root

value.value: A central root cap that is part of a root cap of lateral root.

label.value: lateral root cap of lateral root

value.value: A lateral root cap that is part of a root cap of lateral root.

label.value: central root cap of primary root

value.value: A central root cap that is part of a root cap of primary root.

label.value: lateral root cap of primary root

value.value: A lateral root cap (PO:0020131) that is part of a root cap (PO:0020123) of a primary root (PO:0020127).
A cardinal organ part (PO:0025001) that is an outgrowth of a root (PO:0009005) and is inhabited by nitrogen-fixing bacteria.

definition.value: Root nodules are a symbiosis between a plant (often, but not exclusively, of the Fabaceae) and bacteria of the genus Rhizobium, Bradyrhizobium, or Azorhizobium.

value.value: A branch (PO:0025073) that is prostrate or trailing, and produces  adventitious nodal roots (PO:0003005) and sometimes erect shoots.

definition.value: The stolon develops from an axillary bud (PO:0004709) and produces adventitious roots (PO:0003005) at the nodes and a terminal aerial stem. That stem then sends out one or more stolons from its axillary buds and the process is reiterated. Stolons may be above ground, as with strawberries, or below ground as in potatoes.

value.value: An enlarged more or less thin-walled leaf pavement cell, present, with other similar cells, in longitudinal rows in leaves of monocots.

definition.value: Also called motor cell because of its presumed participation in the mechanism of rolling and unrolling of leaves. If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf (PO:0009025) or non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075), depending on the species. All annotations for angiosperms, gymnosperms, and pteridophytes should go to vascular leaf and all annotations for bryophytes should go to non-vascular leaf.

value.value: A portion of ground tissue (PO:0025059) centrifugally derived from cork cambium (PO:0005599), non-living at maturity, and having suberized walls.

definition.value: Protective in function because the walls are highly impervious to water.

value.value: A chlorenchyma cell that is part of a mesophyll.
Cells with deposits of silica in them. One of the two types of short cells in the epidermis of grasses and bamboos. It is usually paired with epidermal cork cell.

definition.value: One of two types of short cells in the epidermis of grasses. If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf (PO:0009025).

value.value: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) synthesizing protoplasm and producing new cells by division and with only a primary cell wall.
A meristematic cell (PO:0004010) that by division gives rise to two cells, one of which remains meristematic, while the other is added to the plant body.

definition.value: Initial cells are often part of a portion of tissue that is composed mostly of somewhat older, differentiating cells. The division of an initial cell is often uneven, with the smaller daughter cell remaining meristematic.

value.value: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) that is part of a portion of epidermis (PO:0005679).

label.value: formation of vascular leaflet primordia stage

value.value: A vascular leaf expansion stage (PO:0001052) at which a leaflet primordium (PO:0025481) is initiated on the leaf rachis (PO:0020055) of a compound leaf (PO:0020043).
Stage of gynoecium development defined by differentiation and expansion of carpels.
Stage of gynoecium development defined by the closure of the carpel(s).

definition.value: Closure of the carpel can occur in various ways, by fusion or secretion.

value.value: Epidermal cells at the top of developing style differentiate stigma.
Stage of ovule development defined by differentiation and expansion of ovules.
The earliest stage of seed development immediately following double fertilization.
Stage of seed development characterized by seed growth and differentiation.

A plant embryo development stage (PO:0007631) that occurs during the interval between the transition from radial to bilateral symmetry in a plant embryo proper (PO:0000001) and the onset of either the plant embryo cotyledonary stage (PO:0001078) or the plant embryo coleoptilar stage (PO:0001094).

definition.value: A plant embryo bilateral stage is commonly known as the heart stage in dicotyledonous plants and the transition stage in monocots. Preceded by a plant embryo globular stage (PO:0001185).

value.value: A trichome (PO:0000282) that secretes or sequesters a portion of plant substance (PO:0025161).
A trichome that develops from seed coat epidermis.
A portion of secondary xylem (PO:0005848) that lacks living secondary xylem parenchyma cells (PO:0004525).

definition.value: Heartwood has ceased to function in storage and conduction, and the reserve materials have been removed or converted into heartwood substances. It is generally darker colored than sapwood (PO:0004513) and is found in the center of a shoot axis (PO:0025029) or root (PO:0009005), interior to the sapwood. Heartwood forms at the end of a cell death stage of secondary xylem (PO:0025466).

value.value: A portion of secondary xylem (PO:0005848) that has as parts living secondary xylem parenchyma cells (PO:0004525).

definition.value: Sapwood contains reserve materials and may function in the conduction of water and minerals (xylem sap (PO:0025539)). It is generally lighter colored than the heartwood (PO:0004512) and is located between the heartwood and the vascular cambium (PO:0005598) of a shoot axis (PO:0025029) or root (PO:0009005). Sapwood forms during a secondary xylem development stage (PO:0025427).

value.value: A portion of secondary xylem (PO:0005848) that has as parts a single layer of early wood (PO:0004515) and a single layer of late wood (PO:0004516) from the same growth season and is part of a shoot axis (PO:0025029) or root (PO:0009005).

definition.value: Appears as a ring in a transverse section of plant axis (PO:0025004). May be an annual ring (one growth ring per year) or a false annual ring (more or less than one growth ring per year).

value.value: A portion of secondary xylem (PO:0005848) that is a part of a growth ring (PO:0004514) formed during the early part of a growing season, has lower density than late wood (PO:0004516) of the same growth ring, and has as parts early wood tracheary elements (PO:0025461) with generally larger lumens than the late wood tracheary elements (PO:0025462) of the same growth ring.

definition.value: The transition from early wood to late wood may be gradual and is not always easy to distinguish.

value.value: A portion of secondary xylem (PO:0005848) that is a part of a growth ring (PO:0004514) formed during the later part of a growing season, has higher density than early wood (PO:0004515) of the same growth ring, and has as parts late wood tracheary elements (PO:0025462) with generally smaller lumens than the early wood tracheary elements (PO:0025461) of the same growth ring.

definition.value: The transition from early wood to late wood may be gradual and is not always easy to distinguish.

value.value: A portion of secondary xylem (PO:0005848) that includes the last-formed late wood (PO:0004516) of one growth ring (PO:0004514) and the earliest-formed early wood (PO:0004515) of the next growth ring.

definition.value: Used to describe the boundary area between two adjacent growth rings, which may be distinct or indistinct.

value.value: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) outside the vascular cambium (PO:0005598) or the xylem (PO:0005352); in older trees may be divided into dead outer bark and living inner bark, which consists of secondary phloem (PO:0005043).
A fiber cell (PO:0025407) that is part of a portion of phloem (PO:0005417) tissue.
A xylem fiber cell (PO:0000274) with simple pits.

definition.value: Libriform fiber cells have simple (unbordered) pits while fiber tracheids (PO:0000355) have bordered pits. Many intermediate forms exist and are generally classified as fiber tracheids (PO:0000355). If both libriform fiber cells and fiber tracheids are present, the libriform fiber cells usually have thicker walls. Libriform fiber cells have a slit-like aperture toward the cell lumen, but no pit cavity.

value.value: A plant fiber cell (PO:0025407) with thin transverse walls (septa), which are formed when mitosis occurs within the cell after development of a secondary cell wall (GO:0009531).

definition.value: A septate fiber septum is composed of the adjacent primary cell walls of two internal cells that arise from mitosis within the septate fiber cell after it has formed a secondary cell wall (GO:0009531).

value.value: Cambium at the outer margin of the xylem cylinder.
Cambium occurring within xylem.
A portion of secondary phloem tissue produced by included vascular cambium.
A parenchyma cell (PO:0000074) that is part of a portion of secondary xylem parenchyma (PO:0004532).
A secondary xylem parenchyma cell (PO:0004525) that is part of a portion of axial secondary xylem parenchyma (PO:0004533).
A parenchyma cell (PO:0000074) that develops from a ray initial (PO:0000082) and is part of a portion of ray secondary xylem parenchyma (PO:0004534).

label.value: upright ray secondary xylem parenchyma cell

value.value: A ray secondary xylem parenchyma cell (PO:0004527) that is oriented with its longest dimension parallel to the plant axis (PO:0025004) in which it is found.

label.value: procumbent ray secondary xylem parenchyma cell

value.value: A ray secondary xylem parenchyma cell (PO:0004527) that is oriented with its longest dimension radial to the plant axis (PO:0025004) in which it is found.
Empty upright ray cell of approximately the same height as the procumbent ray cell and occurring in indeterminate horizontal series usually interspersed among the procumbent cells.
Cell on the margin of, and tending to form a sheath around, the procumbent cells of a multi-seriate ray as seen in tangential section.
A portion of parenchyma (PO:0005421) tissue that is part of a portion of secondary xylem (PO:0005848) and has as parts secondary xylem parenchyma cells (PO:0004525).
A portion of secondary xylem parenchyma (PO:0004532) that is part of an axial system (PO:0025410) and has as parts axial secondary xylem parenchyma cells (PO:0004526).
A portion of secondary xylem parenchyma (PO:0004532) that is part of a ray system (PO:0025411) and has as parts ray secondary xylem parenchyma cells (PO:0004527).

definition.value: Occurs in bands or rays of variable width and height that extend radially in the secondary xylem (PO:0005848) and secondary phloem (PO:0005043) of a plant axis (PO:0025004).
